SIMPLE: witchery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Witchery
<hw>Witch"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Witcheries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sorcery;
enchantment; witchcraft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great Comus,⟦br⟧
Deep skilled in all his mother's <qex>witcheries</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A woman infamous . . . for <qex>witcheries</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fascination; irresistible influence;
enchantment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He never felt⟦br⟧
The <qex>witchery</qex> of the soft blue sky.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The dear, dear <qex>witchery</qex> of song.</q>
<rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Witch-hazel</ent>⟦br⟧
